article.description: Dallas Cameron made two free throws in the final 15 seconds as Stephen F. Austin came from behind to beat Division II Northeastern State 75-70 on Friday night to extend its home-court winning str
article.headline: Stephen F. Austin extends home win streak to 30
article.linkText: Stephen F. Austin extends home win streak to 30
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Dallas Cameron made two free throws in the final 15 seconds as Stephen F. Austin came from behind to beat Division II Northeastern State 75-70 on Friday night to extend its home-court winning streak to 30 games. Northeastern was up 41-31 at the half and was ahead 70-66 with 2:09 remaining. SFA's TJ Holyfield made two free throws and Ivan Canete completed a 3-point play to give the Lumberjacks a 71-70 lead with 28 seconds left. SFA outscored Northeastern 41-29 in the second half. Both teams spent a lot of time at the free throw line as Stephen F. Austin (2-1) made 32 of 36 and the RiverHawks made 22 of 32 free throw attempts. SFA was 20-of-43 shooting while limiting Northeastern to 20 of 63. Holyfield had 17 points and Kevon Harris 16 for the Lumberjacks. Montre Williams and Tyler Williams had 14 points apiece for Northwestern State.
